          name: "Overview of class",
          desc: '"International Wildlife Law & Policy"\n\nMany scientists and policymakers believe that we are on the cusp of the world\'s sixth great extinction spasm, driven almost entirely by anthropogenic factors, including habitat destruction, unsustainable trade, the introduction of invasive species, and the looming specter of climate change. This course explores the role of international law in addressing the biodiversity crisis and efforts to protect wildlife species. An ancillary objective is to provide students with a foundation in international law, including skills in analyzing treaty provisions.',
